    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 7.531,
      "end": 12.376,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit libravox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 13.357,
      "end": 18.382,
      "text": "This reading by Karish Allenberg, www.kray.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 20.304,
      "end": 21.224,
      "text": "Asip's fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 22.165,
      "end": 23.667,
      "text": "The fox and the crow.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 26.729,
      "end": 37.178,
      "text": "A crow was sitting on a branch of a tree with a piece of cheese in her beak when a fox observed her and set his wits to work to discover some way of getting the cheese.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 38.359,
      "end": 44.925,
      "text": "Coming and standing under the tree he looked up and said, What a noble bird I see above me.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 46.221,
      "end": 50.544,
      "text": "Her beauty is without equal, the hue of her plumage exquisite.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 51.245,
      "end": 54.647,
      "text": "If only her voice is as sweet as her looks are fair.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 55.548,
      "end": 58.49,
      "text": "She ought without doubt to be queen of the birds.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 60.232,
      "end": 67.617,
      "text": "The crow was hugely flattered by this, and just to show the fox that she could sing, she gave a loud caa.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 68.958,
      "end": 73.562,
      "text": "Down came the cheese, of course, and the fox, snatching it up, said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 74.678,
      "end": 76.78,
      "text": "You have a voice, madam, I see.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 77.601,
      "end": 79.463,
      "text": "What you want is wits.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 81.806,
      "end": 83.988,
      "text": "End of The Fox and the Crow.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 85.95,
      "end": 91.977,
      "text": "Read by Cara Schalenberg on January 11th, 2006, in Oceanside, California.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
